This paper proposes a technique to accelerate architecture selection for deep neural networks through the use of a HyperNet. The paper focuses on the performance of the proposed method on image classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves the use of memory read-writes, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
